events.description:

events.name: Google Cloud Study Jam on Machine Learning
events.description:
Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers. This is a great opportunity to bring members of your community together to learn something in person. These trainings will give your community members a specific skill they can use for personal development or career advancement.

With a Cloud Study Jam, your community members and you will learn the fundamental tools and capabilities of Google Cloud. Attendees will receive free access to our online labs.

After the session, attendees can continue taking labs to earn Google Cloud badges. Encourage your community to continue learning by holding another session and staying in touch online!
events.how_to_find_us: Landmark : Opp. Hotel Four points Sheraton

events.name: Google Cloud OnBoard OnAir
events.description:
Dear Members,

You are invited to participate in Cloud OnBoard OnAir, a half-day livestream technical training event that will cover core infrastructure fundamentals on Google Cloud Platform. This training will help you get started with cloud services such as:

Compute Engine
Storage and Datastore
Container Engine
Kubernetes Engine
App Engine

This free to attend half-day online event will be delivered by our leading instructors using presentations and demonstrations. You will be provided with industry best practices and tips to further your learning and ability to build with the Google Cloud Platform.

Join us to accelerate your career with GCP by registering using the button below. We encourage you to forward this email invitation to any colleagues you think would benefit from this event.

PLEASE MAKE NOTE THAT THIS IS AN ONLINE EVENT SO YOU CAN ATTEND THIS PROGRAM FROM OFFICE / HOME. YOU ARE NOT REQUIRED TO GATHER AT ANY PARTICULAR VENUE.

THANKS
